Murang'a Public Service Board chairman Titus Waithaka is dead. Waithaka was involved in a grisly accident near Safari Park Hotel, Nairobi on Sunday morning. His official car was ripped apart by a guard rail on Thika Road, killing him instantly. Police said they were called to the scene long after the accident had happened. The body was moved to the mortuary. The accident played out like that which claimed the life of Nyeri Governor Wahome Gakuru whose car was ripped apart by a guard rail. Kenyans have asked the highways authority to relook at the guard rails terming them 'death traps'.  /COURTESY Click here for the latest political news    